de/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/routes/lifecycle.py:\n  Line 5: * ``POST /admin/lifecycle/fanout/<action>`` — cron-fired entry point.\n\n  Line 10:   Body ``{\"org_id\": \"...\"}``. Same downstream code path as the fanout\n\n  Line 13: Auth: admin-key only (``auth.enforce_admin``). The fanout route is\n\n  Line 32:     publish_insights_request,\n\n  Line 60:     # Periodic discovery insights. Consumer also lives in core-api and\n\n  Line 62:     \"insights\": publish_insights_request,\n\n  Line 66: # fanout loop. Each pair = 1 HTTP POST to core-storage-api + 1 Pub/Sub\n\n  Line 70: # enough that the storage-writer pool is never saturated by fanout\n\n  Line 76:     \"\"\"Discovery query for the fanout — purge is the odd action here:\n\n  Line 138: @router.post(\"/admin/lifecycle/fanout/{action}\")\n\n  Line 139: async def fanout_lifecycle_action(\n\n  Line 187:                 \"lifecycle fanout: failed to trigger one org; continuing\",\n\n  Line 196:         \"lifecycle fanout dispatched\",\n\n  Line 216:     downstream as the fanout-loop body. ``triggered_by`` records who\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/organization_settings.py:\n  Line 93:     # Periodic discovery insights (lifecycle-insights cron). Opt-in:\n\n  Line 97:     # wants the daily ``generate_insights(focus='discover')`` pass.\n\n  Line 100:     # insights run, so even an enabled tenant pays only when the\n\n  Line 102:     \"insights\": {\n\n  Line 103:         \"auto_insights_enabled\": None,\n\n  Line 331:     \"insights.auto_insights_enabled\": bool,\n\n  Line 558:     def auto_insights_enabled(self) -> bool:\n\n  Line 559:         val = self._ts.get(\"insights\", {}).get(\"auto_insights_enabled\")\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/